I&rsquo;m incapable of not devolving into politeness with unfeeling and unconvincingly robotic digital assistants. I can&rsquo;t imagine how much worse it will get when they get smarter and more natural.
Yesterday I literally said, &ldquo;Hey Siri, you can turn the music off if you want. I&rsquo;m stepping out.&rdquo;
IF YOU WANT&hellip;

 Me: &quot;Hey Siri, play some good music&quot;
Siri: &quot;Ok, here are some popular hits&quot;
Siri: [plays some hip hop stuff with lots of &quot;n&quot; words and commentary on female anatomy, which immediately makes me uncomfortable in my private office.]
