@imc&rsquo;s high school has a cool tradition called Senior Tribute Night where the teaches prepare a roughly 2 minute speech about each and every graduating senior. Students and parents then get to hear smart, heartfelt, funny tributes to all these awesome kids. Isabel&rsquo;s beloved music teacher did hers. It was so sweet. Here are some things she said.
Although limited to two minutes, &ldquo;I could very easily talk for weeks on end about this super-human.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I had to fight off others — and I fought hard — to get to be the one to talk about her tonight. She is that respected by her teachers.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Isabel could very well be one of the most passionate students I&rsquo;ve ever taught.&rdquo;
&ldquo;My experience with her in the five years I&rsquo;ve known her is that everything she does, she does with great passion.&rdquo;
&ldquo;She is passionate about everything. Fashion. Food. Music. Books. Hamilton. Mr. Hjelmberg&rsquo;s humane letters class&hellip; &quot;
[pause for laughter]
&ldquo;She is even PASSIONATE about organized choir folders.&rdquo; After asking her to help organize my music folder &ldquo;it was returned to me with color coded labels for every song type, and a sweet note in the front.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Isabel is passionate about her studies. Sometimes too passionate. Often thinking the worst of her abilities and doubting her accomplishments. It&rsquo;s at those times that I get the many expressions of Isabel&hellip;&rdquo;
Here she held up giant posters of various exasperated emoji faces to go with Isabel&rsquo;s various frustrations including &ldquo;I failed my physics test&rdquo; 😧, &ldquo;I&rsquo;m so stressed out&rdquo; 😫 and &ldquo;I wish the rest of the choir would shut their mouths and rehearse&rdquo; 😡.
